<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 2:52PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Perry
and northwestern Stone Counties through 330 PM CDT...
At 251 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 9 miles west of Perkinston, or 12 miles southwest
of Wiggins, moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wiggins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
